trend_summary: Across the series, forest-dominated terrain gradually gives way to more patchy farmland and a modestly enlarging town at the north-east tip. Linear road and utility corridors extend, and scattered forestry clear-cuts appear, some later showing partial regrowth. Built-up surfaces grow slowly, so the landscape remains chiefly rural and green.
notable_changes: Visible outward growth and infilling of the north-eastern town core.
New or widened roads/linear clearings weaving between hamlets.
Expansion of agricultural fields at the expense of surrounding woodland.
Emergence of large rectangular forestry clear-cuts in central and western sectors.
Signs of vegetation regrowth on some previously cleared patches.
